    <figure>
      <img alt="Photo collage of the Apple Pay logo over a grainy image of crumpled money." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/h-mVNtDBfrqJVFYrk-0_YZHlEuo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73660047/STK274_APPLE_PAY_CVirginia.0.jpg" />
        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge, Getty Images</figcaption>
    </figure>

  <p id="eS1nYx">Apple Pay will now <a href="https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/10/apple-celebrates-10-years-of-apple-pay/">include Klarna as an option</a> at checkout. The addition of the buy now pay later (BNPL) service comes just months after <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/17/24180340/apple-pay-later-shutting-down-months-after-launch">Apple shut down Pay Later</a>, its own BNPL service launched in 2023.</p>
<p id="30q38E">Klarna lets users purchase products with four interest-free installments. Even though BNPL services like <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/05/28/buy-now-pay-later-loans-are-second-only-to-credit-cards-in-popularity.html">Klarna are rising</a> in popularity, <a href="https://www.bankrate.com/loans/personal-loans/buy-now-pay-later-survey/?tpt=b">surveys suggest the services</a> may lead to overspending.</p>
<figure class="e-image">
        
      <cite>Image: Apple</cite>
  </figure>
<p id="QXwcFt">These loans are also <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/06/20/why-buy-now-pay-later-debt-could-become-a-problem-for-us-economy.html">harder to track</a> because most aren’t reported to credit bureaus. Earlier this year, the <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/23/24163384/buy-now-pay-later-services-bnpl-credit-card-rules">Consumer Financial Protection Bureau issued a rule</a> that classifies BNPL services as credit card providers, requiring them to investigate disputed purchases and provide refunds for returned products.</p>
